  "description": "Judicial review is the power of courts to examine legislation or executive action and declare it invalid if it conflicts with a constitution or higher law. It is the enforcement mechanism of [constitutionalism](./constitutionalism.md): without judicial review, constitutional limits are aspirational rather than binding.",
